  "output": "Got full picture. Here's the analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Coverage Gaps\n\n### 1. `order_processor.py` — Zero direct unit tests\n\nAll four functions (`advance_shipments`, `fulfill_orders`, `place_orders`, `accrue_costs`) are tested only indirectly via `process_round`. Every sub-scenario is invisible to the test suite.\n\n**a) `advance_shipments` gaps:**\n\n```python\n# tests/core/test_order_processor.py\n\nimport pytest\nfrom core.engine.order_processor import advance_shipments, fulfill_orders, place_orders, accrue_costs\nfrom core.models import GameState, PlayerRole, PlayerState, GameConfig, IncomingShipment, GamePhase\n\n\ndef make_state(**kwargs):\n    cfg = GameConfig(**{k: v for k, v in kwargs.items() if k in GameConfig.model_fields})\n    players = {\n        role: PlayerState(role=role, inventory=12, backlog=0)\n        for role in PlayerRole\n    }\n    return GameState(game_id=\"test\", config=cfg, players=players, phase=GamePhase.ACTIVE)\n\n\ndef test_advance_shipments_delivers_arriving():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments = [\n        IncomingShipment(quantity=6, arrives_in_rounds=1),\n    ]\n    state = advance_shipments(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory == 18\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments == []\n\n\ndef test_advance_shipments_decrements_timer():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments = [\n        IncomingShipment(quantity=6, arrives_in_rounds=2),\n    ]\n    state = advance_shipments(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory == 12  # not yet arrived\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments[0].arrives_in_rounds == 1\n\n\ndef test_advance_shipments_multiple_arrivals():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments = [\n        IncomingShipment(quantity=3, arrives_in_rounds=1),\n        IncomingShipment(quantity=4, arrives_in_rounds=1),\n    ]\n    state = advance_shipments(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory == 19  # 12 + 3 + 4\n\n\ndef test_advance_shipments_empty_pipeline():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments = []\n    state = advance_shipments(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory == 12\n```\n\n**b) `fulfill_orders` gaps:**\n\n```python\ndef test_fulfill_orders_partial_fills_backlog():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 3\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog = 0\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 0 for role in PlayerRole}\n    state = fulfill_orders(state, customer_demand=8)\n    # can only ship 3, backlog = 8 - 3 = 5\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog == 5\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory == 0\n\n\ndef test_fulfill_orders_clears_existing_backlog():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 20\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog = 5\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 0 for role in PlayerRole}\n    state = fulfill_orders(state, customer_demand=4)\n    # demand=4 + backlog=5 = 9, inventory=20 → ships 9, backlog=0, inv=11\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog == 0\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory == 11\n\n\ndef test_fulfill_orders_creates_downstream_shipment():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 4 for role in PlayerRole}\n    initial_shipments = len(state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments)\n    state = fulfill_orders(state, customer_demand=4)\n    # Wholesaler should have sent a shipment to Retailer\n    assert len(state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments) > initial_shipments\n\n\ndef test_fulfill_orders_shipment_uses_config_delay():\n    state = make_state(shipping_delay=3)\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 4 for role in PlayerRole}\n    before = len(state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments)\n    state = fulfill_orders(state, customer_demand=0)\n    new = [s for s in state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments]\n    added = [s for s in new if s.arrives_in_rounds == 3]\n    assert len(added) > 0\n\n\ndef test_fulfill_orders_zero_demand_no_backlog():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 0 for role in PlayerRole}\n    state = fulfill_orders(state, customer_demand=0)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog == 0\n```\n\n**c) `place_orders` gaps:**\n\n```python\ndef test_place_orders_updates_last_order():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 5 for role in PlayerRole}\n    state = place_orders(state)\n    for role in PlayerRole:\n        assert state.players[role].last_order == 5\n\n\ndef test_place_orders_passes_to_upstream_incoming_orders():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.orders_this_round = {PlayerRole.RETAILER: 7}\n    state = place_orders(state)\n    assert 7 in state.players[PlayerRole.WHOLESALER].incoming_orders\n\n\ndef test_place_orders_factory_schedules_self_shipment():\n    state = make_state(order_delay=2)\n    state.orders_this_round = {PlayerRole.FACTORY: 10}\n    before = len(state.players[PlayerRole.FACTORY].incoming_shipments)\n    state = place_orders(state)\n    after = state.players[PlayerRole.FACTORY].incoming_shipments\n    new_shipments = [s for s in after[before:] if s.quantity == 10 and s.arrives_in_rounds == 2]\n    assert len(new_shipments) == 1\n\n\ndef test_place_orders_zero_order():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.orders_this_round = {role: 0 for role in PlayerRole}\n    state = place_orders(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].last_order == 0\n```\n\n**d) `accrue_costs` gaps:**\n\n```python\ndef test_accrue_costs_uses_config_values():\n    state = make_state(holding_cost=1.0, backlog_cost=2.0)\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 10\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog = 3\n    state = accrue_costs(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].cumulative_cost == pytest.approx(16.0)  # 10*1 + 3*2\n\n\ndef test_accrue_costs_zero_inventory_zero_backlog():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 0\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog = 0\n    prior = state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].cumulative_cost\n    state = accrue_costs(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].cumulative_cost == prior\n\n\ndef test_accrue_costs_accumulates():\n    state = make_state()\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 4\n    state = accrue_costs(state)\n    state = accrue_costs(state)\n    # 4 * 0.5 * 2 = 4.0\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].cumulative_cost == pytest.approx(4.0)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `GameConfig` — untested fields\n\n```python\n# add to tests/core/test_models.py\n\ndef test_game_config_shipping_and_order_delay():\n    cfg = GameConfig(shipping_delay=3, order_delay=4)\n    assert cfg.shipping_delay == 3\n    assert cfg.order_delay == 4\n\n\ndef test_game_config_invalid_delays():\n    with pytest.raises(Exception):\n        GameConfig(shipping_delay=0)\n    with pytest.raises(Exception):\n        GameConfig(order_delay=0)\n\n\ndef test_game_config_custom_costs():\n    cfg = GameConfig(holding_cost=1.5, backlog_cost=3.0)\n    assert cfg.holding_cost == 1.5\n    assert cfg.backlog_cost == 3.0\n\n\ndef test_game_config_demand_wraps_in_engine():\n    \"\"\"Engine wraps demand_pattern with modulo — shorter pattern is valid.\"\"\"\n    from core.engine.game_engine import GameEngine\n    cfg = GameConfig(num_rounds=6, demand_pattern=[2, 4])  # only 2 values, 6 rounds\n    engine = GameEngine()\n    state = engine.create_game(cfg, ai_roles=set(PlayerRole))\n    state = engine.start_game(state)\n    from core.ai_players.rule_based import ConstantOrderAI\n    for _ in range(6):\n        for role in PlayerRole:\n            state = engine.submit_order(state, role, ConstantOrderAI(role).decide_order(state))\n        state = engine.process_round(state)\n    assert state.customer_demand_history == [2, 4, 2, 4, 2, 4]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `GameState.is_round_complete` — all-human edge case\n\n```python\ndef test_game_state_round_complete_all_human_none_submitted():\n    state = GameState(\n        game_id=\"test\",\n        players={\n            role: PlayerState(role=role, inventory=12, backlog=0, is_ai=False)\n            for role in PlayerRole\n        },\n    )\n    assert not state.is_round_complete()\n\n\ndef test_game_state_round_complete_all_human_all_submitted():\n    state = GameState(\n        game_id=\"test\",\n        players={\n            role: PlayerState(role=role, inventory=12, backlog=0, is_ai=False)\n            for role in PlayerRole\n        },\n    )\n    for role in PlayerRole:\n        state.orders_this_round[role] = 4\n    assert state.is_round_complete()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `GameEngine` — missing edge cases\n\n```python\n# add to tests/core/test_engine.py\n\ndef test_create_game_pipeline_prefill(engine):\n    cfg = GameConfig(shipping_delay=3, initial_inventory=12)\n    state = engine.create_game(cfg)\n    for ps in state.players.values():\n        assert len(ps.incoming_shipments) == 3\n        assert all(s.quantity == 6 for s in ps.incoming_shipments)\n\n\ndef test_create_game_id_is_uuid(engine):\n    import uuid\n    state = engine.create_game()\n    uuid.UUID(state.game_id)  # raises if not valid UUID\n\n\ndef test_create_game_unique_ids(engine):\n    s1 = engine.create_game()\n    s2 = engine.create_game()\n    assert s1.game_id != s2.game_id\n\n\ndef test_process_round_on_finished_raises(engine):\n    from core.ai_players.rule_based import ConstantOrderAI\n    cfg = GameConfig(num_rounds=1)\n    state = engine.create_game(cfg, ai_roles=set(PlayerRole))\n    state = engine.start_game(state)\n    for role in PlayerRole:\n        state = engine.submit_order(state, role, ConstantOrderAI(role).decide_order(state))\n    state = engine.process_round(state)\n    assert state.phase == GamePhase.FINISHED\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n        engine.process_round(state)\n\n\ndef test_submit_order_duplicate_role_overwrites(engine):\n    state = engine.create_game()\n    state = engine.start_game(state)\n    state = engine.submit_order(state, PlayerRole.RETAILER, 4)\n    state = engine.submit_order(state, PlayerRole.RETAILER, 9)\n    assert state.orders_this_round[PlayerRole.RETAILER] == 9\n\n\ndef test_get_visible_state_contains_incoming_shipments(engine, all_ai_game):\n    visible = engine.get_visible_state(all_ai_game, PlayerRole.RETAILER)\n    assert \"incoming_shipments\" in visible\n    assert isinstance(visible[\"incoming_shipments\"], list)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Bug: `PlayerState.round_cost()` uses module constants, not config\n\n`round_cost()` at `game.py:42` hardcodes `HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT` / `BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT`. `accrue_costs()` at `order_processor.py:87` uses `state.config.holding_cost`. They diverge with custom config. This should be a test that exposes the inconsistency:\n\n```python\ndef test_round_cost_inconsistency_with_custom_config():\n    \"\"\"round_cost() ignores config — uses module constants. accrue_costs() uses config.\"\"\"\n    from core.engine.order_processor import accrue_costs\n    state = make_state(holding_cost=1.0, backlog_cost=2.0)\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 10\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog = 0\n    # round_cost() returns 10 * 0.5 = 5.0 (ignores config)\n    ps = state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER]\n    assert ps.round_cost() == 5.0  # module constant, NOT config\n    state = accrue_costs(state)\n    assert state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].cumulative_cost == 10.0  # uses config\n    # These should be equal but aren't — this test documents the divergence\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `OrderUpToAI` — pipeline counting\n\n```python\ndef test_order_up_to_counts_pipeline(active_state):\n    \"\"\"Pipeline stock reduces order — AI sees in-transit units.\"\"\"\n    state = active_state\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].inventory = 0\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].backlog = 0\n    state.players[PlayerRole.RETAILER].incoming_shipments = [\n        IncomingShipment(quantity=16, arrives_in_rounds=1)\n    ]\n    ai = OrderUpToAI(PlayerRole.RETAILER)\n    # position = 0 - 0 + 16 = 16, target = 16 → order = 0\n    assert ai.decide_order(state) == 0\n\n\ndef test_order_up_to_cannot_instantiate_base():\n    from core.ai_players.base import BaseAIPlayer\n    with pytest.raises(TypeError):\n        BaseAIPlayer(PlayerRole.RETAILER)  # type: ignore\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of gaps by priority\n\n| Priority | Gap | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| High | `order_processor.py` has zero direct tests | Core fulfillment logic; indirect testing misses delay/partial-fill bugs |\n| High | `round_cost()` vs `accrue_costs()` constant divergence | Silent cost reporting bug with custom config |\n| High | `process_round()` on FINISHED state not tested | No guard verified |\n| Medium | `GameConfig` delay/cost fields untested | Validators untested, custom config silently broken |\n| Medium | Pipeline pre-fill count/quantity not verified | Engine setup bug would be invisible |\n| Medium | Factory self-shipment with `order_delay` not tested | Production scheduling path unverified |\n| Low | `game_id` UUID validity/uniqueness | Minor but important for multiplayer |\n| Low | `BaseAIPlayer` abstract instantiation | ABC contract untested |\n",
